article.headline: Ark. Little Rock 71, W. Kentucky 69
article.story: LITTLE ROCK (AP) -- De'Andre Eggins scored 23 points to lift Arkansas-Little Rock to a close 71-69 victory over Western Kentucky in Sun Belt Conference play Wednesday. Eggins and Steven Moore each had three assists, and Terrance Akins added 13 points. Rash Jones-Jennings scored ten for UALR (9-11 overall, 4-5 SBC). The Trojans were up by six at the half, 35-29, before Western Kentucky (14-6, 6-2) narrowed the margin even further. A.J. Slaughter led Western Kentucky with 14 points. Tyrone Brazelton scored 13 points, including 2-of-4 three pointers, and led with five assists. Jeremy Evans added 12.
